original_title: Living History: Fishing Alaska’s Waterfall Resort
overview: Buckle up for adventure as we take you to Alaska’s world-class Waterfall Resort on Prince of Wales Island, west of Ketchikan, following a visit to the original Deadliest Catch Boat, the Sea Star. Known the world over for its unparalleled king and silver salmon, halibut and lingcod fishing, this resort and former cannery oozes history and boasts the largest private fishing fleet in Alaska.
title: Living History: Fishing Alaska’s Waterfall Resort
